  "prob_desc_notes": "Note\"mew\" is not a palindrome, so the longest substring of it that is not a palindrome, is the string \"mew\" itself. Thus, the answer for the first example is $$$3$$$.The string \"uffuw\" is one of the longest non-palindrome substrings (of length $$$5$$$) of the string \"wuffuw\", so the answer for the second example is $$$5$$$.All substrings of the string \"qqqqqqqq\" consist of equal characters so they are palindromes. This way, there are no non-palindrome substrings. Thus, the answer for the third example is $$$0$$$.",
