  "prob_desc_output_spec": "If there is such a substring in $$$s$$$ that is not a palindrome, print the maximum length of such a substring. Otherwise print $$$0$$$. Note that there can be multiple longest substrings that are not palindromes, but their length is unique.",
  "source_code": "#include <stdio.h>\n#include <string.h>\n\nint main()\n{\n    int i,n;\n    char ch,s[50];\n    scanf(\"%s\",s);\n    ch=s[0];\n    n=strlen(s);\n    for(i=0;i<n;i++)\n    {\n        if(s[i]!=s[n-1-i])\n        {\n            printf(\"%d\",n);\n            return 0;\n        }\n    }\n    for(i=0;i<n;i++)\n    {\n        if(ch!=s[i])\n        {\n            printf(\"%d\",n-1);\n            return 0;\n        }\n    }\n    printf(\"0\");\n    return 0;\n}",
